<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Mod on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/mod/</link><description>Recent content in Mod on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/mod/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Go go.mod File Not Found Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-not-found-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-not-found-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="gomod-file-not-found-error-fix"&gt;go.mod File Not Found Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;go.mod file not found&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when Go commands are run outside of a Go module and module mode is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since Go 1.11, the Go toolchain uses modules for dependency management. Commands like &lt;code&gt;go build&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;go test&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;go get&lt;/code&gt; expect to find a &lt;code&gt;go.mod&lt;/code&gt; file in the current directory or a parent directory. Without it, Go may fall back to GOPATH mode (deprecated) or fail entirely.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go go.mod File Not Found Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-not-found/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-not-found/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="go-gomod-file-not-found--fix"&gt;Go: go.mod File Not Found — Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &amp;ldquo;go.mod file not found&amp;rdquo; error occurs when you run Go commands in a directory that isn&amp;rsquo;t part of a Go module and has no &lt;code&gt;go.mod&lt;/code&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since Go 1.11, Go modules are the standard dependency management system. Every Go project must have a &lt;code&gt;go.mod&lt;/code&gt; file in its root directory (or a parent directory). Without it, commands like &lt;code&gt;go build&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;go run&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;go test&lt;/code&gt; fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go go.mod Version Mismatch Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-version/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-version/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="go-gomod-requires-go--x--fix"&gt;Go: go.mod Requires Go &amp;gt;= X — Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A go.mod version mismatch error occurs when the Go version specified in &lt;code&gt;go.mod&lt;/code&gt; is higher than the installed Go toolchain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;go&lt;/code&gt; directive in &lt;code&gt;go.mod&lt;/code&gt; specifies the minimum Go version required to build the module. If your installed Go version is older than what &lt;code&gt;go.mod&lt;/code&gt; requires, commands fail with &lt;code&gt;go: go.mod requires go &amp;gt;= X (running go Y)&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cloning a project requiring newer Go&lt;/strong&gt; — your Go is outdated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Multiple developers with different Go versions&lt;/strong&gt; — team uses different versions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CI/CD environment&lt;/strong&gt; — build server has older Go than development machine.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New go.mod directive&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;go 1.21&lt;/code&gt; toolchain directive was added.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: Installed Go is too old&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go version
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go version go1.20 linux/amd64&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cat go.mod
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go 1.21 # Requires Go 1.21+&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go build
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go: go.mod requires go &amp;gt;= 1.21 (running go 1.20)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: go.mod specifies exact version&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cat go.mod
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go 1.21.0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Your Go is 1.21.1 — this should work, but sometimes patch versions matter&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 3: Toolchain directive&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cat go.mod
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go 1.21&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# toolchain go1.21.5&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Go 1.21 without the patch version may not satisfy toolchain requirement&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-update-go-to-the-required-version"&gt;Fix 1: Update Go to the required version&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check current version&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go version
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Download and install latest Go&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Visit https://go.dev/dl/ or use:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go install golang.org/dl/go1.21.0@latest
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or update via package manager&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo snap refresh go
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# or&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;brew upgrade go
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-downgrade-gomod-to-match-installed-go"&gt;Fix 2: Downgrade go.mod to match installed Go&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// go.mod&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;module&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;github&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;username&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;myproject&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;go&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1.20&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Changed from 1.21 to 1.20&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-the-gotoolchain-environment-variable"&gt;Fix 3: Use the GOTOOLCHAIN environment variable&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Allow automatic toolchain download&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;GOTOOLCHAIN&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;auto go build
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or specify exact toolchain&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;GOTOOLCHAIN&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;go1.21.0 go build
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-remove-toolchain-directive-if-not-needed"&gt;Fix 4: Remove toolchain directive if not needed&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// go.mod — before&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;module&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;github&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;username&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;myproject&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;go&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1.21&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;toolchain&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;go1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;.21.5&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// go.mod — after&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;module&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;github&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;username&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;myproject&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;go&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1.21&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-5-use-go-mod-edit-to-change-version"&gt;Fix 5: Use go mod edit to change version&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Change go version in go.mod&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go mod edit -go&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;1.20
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Verify&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cat go.mod
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go 1.20&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Tidy dependencies&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go mod tidy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# This triggers: go: go.mod requires go &amp;gt;= 1.21 (running go 1.20)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go version
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go version go1.20 linux/amd64&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cat go.mod
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go 1.21&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go build
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go: go.mod requires go &amp;gt;= 1.21 (running go 1.20)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-not-found/"&gt;go-mod-not-found&lt;/a&gt; — go.mod file not found.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-sum-mismatch/"&gt;go-sum-mismatch&lt;/a&gt; — go.sum checksum mismatch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/package-not-found/"&gt;package-not-found&lt;/a&gt; — required package not found.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go go.mod Version Mismatch Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-version-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-version-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="gomod-version-mismatch-error-fix"&gt;go.mod Version Mismatch Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;go.mod requires go &amp;gt;= X&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when the &lt;code&gt;go&lt;/code&gt; directive in &lt;code&gt;go.mod&lt;/code&gt; specifies a version higher than the installed Go toolchain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;go.mod&lt;/code&gt; file contains a &lt;code&gt;go&lt;/code&gt; directive specifying the minimum Go version required by the module. When you run Go commands with an older toolchain, it refuses to build because it may not support features used by the module. Go 1.21+ added the &lt;code&gt;toolchain&lt;/code&gt; directive for automatic toolchain downloading.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go go.sum Mismatch Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-sum-mismatch-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-sum-mismatch-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="gosum-mismatch-error-fix"&gt;go.sum Mismatch Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;go.sum mismatch&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when the checksums in &lt;code&gt;go.sum&lt;/code&gt; don&amp;rsquo;t match the downloaded module contents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go&amp;rsquo;s module system uses &lt;code&gt;go.sum&lt;/code&gt; to verify that downloaded modules haven&amp;rsquo;t been tampered with. Each module version has an expected hash. When a module&amp;rsquo;s contents don&amp;rsquo;t match the stored hash, Go refuses to proceed. The Go checksum database (&lt;code&gt;sum.golang.org&lt;/code&gt;) provides authoritative hashes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Corrupted download&lt;/strong&gt; — network issue during module download.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Module republished&lt;/strong&gt; — author re-tagged the same version with different content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manual go.sum edit&lt;/strong&gt; — someone modified go.sum incorrectly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proxy inconsistency&lt;/strong&gt; — module proxy serves different content than origin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Private module with wrong sum&lt;/strong&gt; — internal module with stale checksum.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: Corrupted module cache&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go mod download
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go.sum mismatch&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Module content changed after tag&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Author force-pushed a tag&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go mod tidy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go.sum mismatch for module@v1.2.3&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 3: Manual go.sum edit&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Someone removed or modified entries in go.sum&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go build
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go.sum mismatch&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 4: Private module proxy issues&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;GONOSUMCHECK&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;private.company.com go mod download
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Still gets mismatch if local cache is stale&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-delete-and-regenerate-gosum"&gt;Fix 1: Delete and regenerate go.sum&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm go.sum
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go mod tidy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-clear-module-cache"&gt;Fix 2: Clear module cache&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go clean -modcache
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go mod download
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-gonosumdb-for-private-modules"&gt;Fix 3: Use GONOSUMDB for private modules&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Skip checksum database for private modules&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;export GONOSUMDB&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;private.company.com
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;export GONOSUMCHECK&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;private.company.com
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go mod tidy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-gonosumcheck-for-specific-modules"&gt;Fix 4: Use GONOSUMCHECK for specific modules&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Skip sum check for specific module&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;GONOSUMCHECK&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;github.com/myorg/mymodule go mod tidy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# This triggers: go: go.sum mismatch&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# (after manually editing go.sum or corrupted cache)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;invalid&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt; go.sum
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;go build ./...
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# go.sum has unexpected content&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-not-found/"&gt;go-mod-not-found&lt;/a&gt; — go.mod file not found.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/go-mod-version/"&gt;go-mod-version&lt;/a&gt; — go.mod requires newer Go version.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/package-not-found/"&gt;package-not-found&lt;/a&gt; — required module provides no package.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go Package Not Found Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/package-not-found-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/package-not-found-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="package-not-found-error-fix"&gt;Package Not Found Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;no required module provides package&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when Go cannot find a module that provides an imported package.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When Go encounters an &lt;code&gt;import&lt;/code&gt; statement, it looks for the package in the module cache, vendor directory, and standard library. If the package isn&amp;rsquo;t found in any location, Go reports which package is missing. This often happens after adding a new import without running &lt;code&gt;go mod tidy&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>